    <sectionbreak sectionType="CONTINUOUS" contentDirection="LEFT_TO_RIGHT" columnSeparatorStyle="NONE" />
    <title headingId="h.oxkdmw4vtq9p">
      <t>ExtraSuite Docs</t>
    </title>
    <subtitle headingId="h.cfu8jobxi8qt">
      <t>The AI-native workflow for Google Workspace</t>
    </subtitle>
    <p />
    <h1 headingId="h.zbtwfdtrogis">
      <t>What is ExtraSuite?</t>
    </h1>
    <p>
      <t>
        <b>ExtraSuite</b>
      </t>
      <t> is an open-source CLI tool built for AI agents. It provides a secure, token-efficient, and auditable way to read and write Google Workspace files — Docs, Sheets, Slides, and Forms — using a simple </t>
      <t>
        <b>pull / edit / push</b>
      </t>
      <t> workflow.</t>
    </p>
    <p>
      <t>Instead of navigating the complex Google APIs directly, agents work with plain files on disk. ExtraSuite handles the translation between those files and the live Google document.</t>
    </p>
    <p />
    <h1 headingId="h.l634pntrm77k">
      <t>How It Works</t>
    </h1>
    <p>
      <t>The core workflow has four steps:</t>
    </p>
    <li parent="kix.9bp6nf50qd7c">
      <t>
        <b>Pull</b>
      </t>
      <t> — Download the Google file and convert it into a local folder of readable files.</t>
    </li>
    <li parent="kix.9bp6nf50qd7c">
      <t>
        <b>Edit</b>
      </t>
      <t> — Modify the local files directly. No API knowledge required.</t>
    </li>
    <li parent="kix.9bp6nf50qd7c">
      <t>
        <b>Diff</b>
      </t>
      <t> — Preview what changes will be sent to Google. No network calls.</t>
    </li>
    <li parent="kix.9bp6nf50qd7c">
      <t>
        <b>Push</b>
      </t>
      <t> — Apply the changes to the live Google document via the API.</t>
    </li>
    <p />
    <h1 headingId="h.et03zk8i68v1">
      <t>Key Innovations</t>
    </h1>
    <p />
    <h2 headingId="h.7quky6p4yop5">
      <t>Git-like Workflow</t>
    </h2>
    <p>
      <t>ExtraSuite brings a </t>
      <t>
        <b>git-inspired pull/diff/push</b>
      </t>
      <t> model to all Google Drive file types. Every pull captures a pristine snapshot so the diff engine knows exactly what changed.</t>
    </p>
    <h2 headingId="h.9n0p2kx5hiyp">
      <t>Unique Agent Identity</t>
    </h2>
    <p>
      <t>Each employee's agent gets a </t>
      <t>
        <b>dedicated 1:1 service account</b>
      </t>
      <t>. The agent only has access to files explicitly shared with it. All changes appear in Google Drive's version history under that identity.</t>
    </p>
    <h2 headingId="h.msjovhfwlkeo">
      <t>Secure Token Handling</t>
    </h2>
    <p>
      <t>Agents </t>
      <t>
        <i>never</i>
      </t>
      <t> see raw tokens. The ExtraSuite server issues short-lived credentials using OIDC and domain-wide delegation. Tokens are cached locally and refreshed automatically.</t>
    </p>
    <h2 headingId="h.c2eiv4ez7cjh">
      <t>Token Efficient</t>
    </h2>
    <p>
      <t>Files are serialized into compact, </t>
      <t>
        <b>LLM-readable formats</b>
      </t>
      <t> — XML for Docs, TSV for Sheets, SML for Slides — so agents consume fewer tokens than working with raw API JSON.</t>
    </p>
    <p />
    <h1 headingId="h.erac3k7o5pvz">
      <t>Supported Modules</t>
    </h1>
    <li parent="kix.vxusmbxxnxzu">
      <t>
        <b>extradoc</b>
      </t>
      <t> — Google Docs with full paragraph, table, and list support</t>
    </li>
    <li parent="kix.vxusmbxxnxzu">
      <t>
        <b>extrasheet</b>
      </t>
      <t> — Google Sheets with formula and formatting support</t>
    </li>
    <li parent="kix.vxusmbxxnxzu">
      <t>
        <b>extraslide</b>
      </t>
      <t> — Google Slides with shape and layout support</t>
    </li>
    <li parent="kix.vxusmbxxnxzu">
      <t>
        <b>extraform</b>
      </t>
      <t> — Google Forms for reading and editing form questions</t>
    </li>
    <li parent="kix.vxusmbxxnxzu">
      <t>
        <b>Gmail</b>
      </t>
      <t> — Draft creation via delegated OAuth</t>
    </li>
    <li parent="kix.vxusmbxxnxzu">
      <t>
        <b>Calendar</b>
      </t>
      <t> — Event management via delegated OAuth</t>
    </li>
    <p />
